18/10/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Belgrade is hosting a conference Monday (October18th) to mark European Anti-Trafficking Day. 
The event, organised by the Serbian parliament, aims to strengthen national mechanisms in the fight against this crime as well as raise public awareness of trafficking. 
The conference brings together representatives of national institutions and the judiciary, experts in the field and international representatives. 
(Tanjug, RTS - 18/10/10)
